Prestmit, which is undoubtedly one of the best app to sell Bitcoin in Nigeria, has just launched its new app. This is another step in the right direction for crypto traders, especially those who use over-the-counter crypto platforms in Africa, knowing that the african continent has topped OTP ecosystem in terms of transaction volume across all regions over the past year. As it is important for a crypto traders to know about the coins they’re investing in, knowing about the platform to use is also necessary. Prestmit has however been seen as a reliable bitcoin trading platform that is genuinely fond of its customers. In February, Prestmit launched a new version of its app to further support cryptocurrency trading in Nigeria. Peradventure you didn’t know much about Prestmit, this post will inform you about the platform as well as its new app. Let’s Talk About Prestmit? Prestmit is a user-centric platform designed for users to trade, buy and sell digital assets as well as gift cards. The platform is notable for its presence in Africa’s most populous nation and fast-rising nation, i.e. Nigeria and Ghana. This makes the Nigerian Naira and Ghanaian Cedis part of the payment options on the platform. What Services Are Offered By Prestmit? <img class="alignnone wp-image-669617" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screenshot_20220303-052324_Office.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="252" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screenshot_20220303-052324_Office.jpg 1021w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screenshot_20220303-052324_Office-300x137.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screenshot_20220303-052324_Office-768x351.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screenshot_20220303-052324_Office-24x11.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screenshot_20220303-052324_Office-36x16.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e